===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|玉|廾|ls=ic|t1=jade|t2=hands}} – to touch jade with one's hands.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|alt=挵,挊}}
Compared with {{cog|km|លួង||to console; to cheer; to coax; to flatter}} < {{cog|okz|lvaṅ||to cheer, amuse, entertain, divert}} < Pre-Angkorian Khmer ''loṅ''. The Khmer initial consonant does not agree with Old Chinese; perhaps the Khmer word is a post-[[Han]] loan ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

